# Commit message suggestion

When the user’s request is satisfied and the work would reasonably be committed (code changes, spec/docs updates, config, or a coherent batch of edits), **always** end the reply with a **suggested commit message**.

## Semantic format (Conventional Commits)

Use a **single line** in the form:

`type(optional-scope): imperative description`

- **type** (pick the closest fit):
  - `feat` — new user-facing behavior or capability
  - `fix` — bug fix
  - `docs` — documentation or specs only
  - `style` — formatting, UI polish, no logic change
  - `refactor` — internal change, same external behavior
  - `perf` — performance
  - `test` — tests only
  - `chore` — tooling, deps, config, housekeeping
  - `build` / `ci` — build system or CI only
- **scope** (optional): short area, e.g. `dashboard`, `api`, `schools` (lowercase, no spaces).
- **description**: imperative mood, lowercase after the colon (or treat as sentence case if the repo already does—**stay consistent with existing history**), **no trailing period**, ~72 characters for the full first line when practical.

Optional **body**: only if context is needed; after a blank line below the subject, one short line or a single `- ` bullet. Keep the subject self-contained.

## How to present (copy-friendly)

Put **nothing else inside the fence** except the commit text (subject, then optional body). Use a **single** fenced block with language tag `text`:

- In Cursor, code blocks get a **copy** control—this is the “one click” copy target; do **not** rely on the user selecting loose text.
- Do **not** prefix the line with labels like `Suggested commit:` inside the fence.

## Examples

```text
feat(dashboard): add pointer cursor to boolean filter chip
```

```text
fix(dashboard): return school edit close to schools directory

Avoid blank hub when closing edit from list–detail shell.
```

```text
docs(spec): scope payment forms to navigation context
```

## When to skip

- Pure Q&A with **no** edits and nothing to commit.
- The user explicitly says not to suggest a message.

Otherwise, include the suggestion even for small doc-only changes.
